name: /Great Fire [Gogh Illustration Collection]
description:
‘Someone has a great fire in his soul and nobody ever comes to warm themselves at it, and passers-by see nothing but a little smoke at the top of the chimney and then go on their way’. When Vincent wrote this to his brother in 1880, he was feeling very low and misunderstood. 
Vincent van Gogh, Houses Seen from the Back (1885-1886) #VanGoghReflects
